---
import ContentLayout from '../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';

const stack = [
  {
    name: 'pwnkit',
    role: 'Detect',
    tagline: 'AI agent pentester',
    description:
      'Fully autonomous agentic pentesting framework. Runs real attacks against web apps, AI/LLM apps, npm packages, and source code. Every finding is independently re-exploited by a blind verify agent to kill false positives.',
    href: 'https://github.com/peaktwilight/pwnkit',
    site: 'https://pwnkit.com',
  },
  {
    name: 'foxguard',
    role: 'Prevent',
    tagline: 'Rust security scanner',
    description:
      'Security scanner as fast as a linter. 100+ built-in rules across 10 languages in a single Rust binary. Sub-second scans mean developers run it on every save, not just in CI.',
    href: 'https://github.com/peaktwilight/foxguard',
    site: 'https://foxguard.dev',
  },
  {
    name: 'opensoar',
    role: 'Respond',
    tagline: 'Python-native SOAR platform',
    description:
      'Open-source orchestration and automation for the modern SOC. Write playbooks in plain Python — no sandboxes, no per-action billing, no vendor lock-in. Sits between your SIEM and your response tools.',
    href: 'https://github.com/opensoar-hq/opensoar-core',
    site: 'https://opensoar.app',
  },
];
---

<ContentLayout
  title="The Open-Source Modern SOC Stack | OpenSOAR"
  description="pwnkit, foxguard, and opensoar — three open-source tools that cover detect, prevent, and respond for the modern security operations center."
  badge="Stack"
  heading="The open-source modern SOC"
  subheading="Three tools. Detect, prevent, respond. All open source, all built to work together."
>
  <p>
    Most security teams stitch together a dozen commercial products to cover the basics. The open-source modern SOC stack gets you the three capabilities that actually matter — finding real vulnerabilities, stopping them before they ship, and responding when something slips through — without the license bill.
  </p>

  <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-1 my-6">
    {stack.map((tool) => (
      <a
        href={tool.href}
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
        class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-surface p-5 transition-colors hover:border-heading/30"
      >
        <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3 mb-2">
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-heading">{tool.name}</h3>
          <span class="indicator indicator--positive">{tool.role}</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-text">{tool.tagline}</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-text leading-relaxed">{tool.description}</p>
      </a>
    ))}
  </div>

  <h2>How they fit together</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>foxguard</strong> runs on every save and every commit, catching hardcoded secrets, SQL injection, XSS, and other well-known patterns before code ever reaches production. It is the fast, cheap first line.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>pwnkit</strong> picks up where static analysis stops. It drives an autonomous AI agent against running applications, chaining real exploits the way a human pentester would, and verifies every finding with a blind re-exploit to eliminate false positives. This is where real IDORs, auth bypasses, and business logic flaws get found.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>opensoar</strong> is the response layer. When an alert fires — from your SIEM, from pwnkit, from anywhere — opensoar runs the Python playbook that triages, enriches, and resolves it. No YAML DSLs, no per-action billing, no vendor lock-in.
  </p>

  <h2>Why open source</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>You can read every line of code that runs against your infrastructure.</li>
    <li>You can self-host, fork, and embed without license negotiations.</li>
    <li>You keep your data, your deployment, and your automation logic.</li>
    <li>You can contribute a rule, a playbook, or an integration and ship it the same day.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Get started</h2>
  <p>
    Each tool installs and runs on its own. Pick whichever one maps to your most painful gap today, and add the others as your stack matures.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://pwnkit.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">pwnkit.com</a> — autonomous pentesting</li>
    <li><a href="https://foxguard.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener">foxguard.dev</a> — fast static scanning</li>
    <li><a href="https://docs.opensoar.app" target="_blank" rel="noopener">docs.opensoar.app</a> — SOAR platform docs</li>
  </ul>
</ContentLayout>
